name: Holywells Park Orchard
short_description: Heritage fruit in a historic landscape.
description: The orchard area near the Conservatory contains a variety of apple, pear, and plum trees open for public harvesting.

name: Orwell Estuary Sea Samphire
short_description: Salty marsh greens along the Orwell.
description: Marsh samphire and sea aster can be found on the tidal mudflats along the Strand (near Freston).

name: Incredible Edible Ipswich - Waterfront
description: Planters located near the University and Waterfront featuring rosemary, mint, and seasonal chard.

name: Christchurch Park Sweet Chestnuts
short_description: Ancient nut trees in the town centre.
description: Large, mature sweet chestnut trees are scattered throughout the upper wooded sections of the park.

name: Giants Hill Hazelnuts
description: Dense hazel thickets along the public footpaths provide a great crop of nuts in late autumn.

name: Chantry Park Blackberries
description: The wilder perimeter of the park, especially near the ponds, is excellent for blackberry picking.

name: River Gipping Wild Garlic
description: Find wild garlic on the damp, shaded banks of the Gipping near the Boss Hall area.

name: Bridge Wood Sloes
description: Gather sloes from the blackthorn bushes along the edge of the wood facing the river.

name: Whitehouse Incredible Edible Planters
description: Raised beds featuring kale, herbs, and strawberries for public picking near the community centre.

name: Belstead Brook Elder
description: Abundant elder bushes for flowers and berries line the valley path.

name: Alexandra Park Rosehips
description: Wild rose bushes in the shrubbery provide rosehips in late autumn.

name: Freston Shore Sea Kale
description: Wild Sea Kale can be found growing in the shingle areas along the estuary banks.

name: Stoke Park Walnuts
description: Mature walnut trees are found in the small woodland patches near the school and residential area.

name: Rushmere Common Gorse
description: Edible gorse flowers can be gathered from the heathland for teas and syrups.

name: Castle Hill Orchard Windfalls
description: Public paths near the historic farmstead areas often yield windfall apples in the autumn.
